# Item-Based Collaborative Filtering Recommendation System

A personalized movie recommendation engine built from scratch in Python using **Item-Based Collaborative Filtering (IBCF)**. The system analyzes historical user rating patterns to calculate item-to-item similarities, predicts user preferences for unrated movies, and generates Top-N recommendations.

## 📌 Features
- **Data Pivoting & Preprocessing:** Transforms raw transaction logs into a dense User-Item interaction matrix.
- **Mean-Centering Normalization:** Eliminates user rating biases (strict vs. lenient raters) to isolate true preferences.
- **Cosine Similarity Architecture:** Computes pairwise directional angles between item vectors to discover underlying item correlations.
- **Weighted Score Prediction:** Utilizes a similarity-weighted average model to project highly accurate ratings for unseen items.
- **Comprehensive Evaluation:** Implements a localized leave-one-out testing validation layer to compute the Mean Absolute Error (MAE).
- **Visual Analytics:** Generates an intuitive item similarity matrix heatmap using Seaborn.

